results.title: Out of the Mouth of Babes
results.description:
Out of the Mouth of Babes

Picture it:  The year - mid 1980’s  Location:  Inside a popular department store in Awesome City, Texas.

As my young daughter and I walked into the store...she quickly inquires, “Mom, what are we going to buy here?”

“I need to find a couple of new bras” I replied.

“Ok” she said.

As I deligently searched thru numerous racks and shelves for the right bra style and size, my daughter asked me,

“Mom, how do you know what size to get?”

“Oh...ok...well...bras are measured by “Cups” from A thru D.  A is the smaller and D is the largest size.

My kid stepped back...looks at me and calmly states: 

“Mom, you don't need a “Cup”...you need “Jugs.”

I smiled at her and said, “Yes, you're probably right.”

I took her hand and said, “Come on sweetie...let's go to the pretzel store and get you your favorite snack.”

Trying extremely hard to contain myself from bursting into laughter as well as tears...her honest and truthful observation of my physical size made me realize it was definitely time to start a diet and exercise regime. 

(this gives a different meaning to "My Cup Runnith Over"...no?)

Esther Monsalve
The Angel Shop

Please note:  the items pictured (launch-time flower arrangements still in progress) are Not for sale in this listing...only one of the many fun times shopping experiences many years ago.  Thank you.

Note: Please use MEMO, an editor writing software, in oder to open this digital file.
